PiperOrigin-RevId: 566462829

`absltest`: do not fail tests on Python 3.12+ when no tests ran and:
- Either test filtering is used
- Or sharding is used and the shard index > 0, i.e. only the first shard will fail when no tests ran on Python 3.12+.

Context: Python 3.12 unittest will now fail when no tests ran after the change from https://github.com/python/cpython/pull/102051. Since `absltest` is built on top of `unittest`, it will follow this behavior change in Python 3.12.

However, when test filtering is used in `absltest`, often used via `bazel test --test_filter=<my_filter>`, the current user expectation is the `bazel test` command should NOT fail is at least one test ran. Since the test runner here has no visibility of the overall `bazel` invocation, we'll make the test not fail when test filtering is used via bazel's environment variable. This is the existing behavior before Python 3.12.

Also test absl-py on Python 3.12.

PiperOrigin-RevId: 565771935

Clean up unit tests that no longer apply for Python 3.12 compatibility.

- `assertDictContainsSubset` is a method from unittest so we don't need to test it. It's also deleted in Python 3.12.
- Migrated the use of deprecated assertion methods. They are also removed in Python 3.12. Some of them are duplicated calls to the deprecated & supported versions of the same method.

PiperOrigin-RevId: 565191723

Explicitly fail when a Mapping or Set object is passed to assertSequenceStartsWith as the `whole` argument.

Previously, when passed a Mapping or Set object, it raises a TypeError. Except starting with Python 3.12, it raises a KeyError for a Mapping object because slice objects are now hashable (i.e. `a_dict[:2]` usually raises a `KeyError`).

This change makes the unexpected inputs fail more explicitly.

PiperOrigin-RevId: 553631709

Update parameterized.CoopTestCase to work with python3 metaclasses.

By setting and accessing __metaclass__, we were not achieving the goals of this
function, which is to make it possible to have both the functionality of
paramterized.TestCase and another TestCase instance with its own metaclass.

Because there are client classes that are using CoopTestCase to combine parameterized.TestCase with another class that isn't using a metaclass we need to support that use-case. We do it by returning a simple multiple inheritance subclass without a combined metaclass, and emit a warning telling the author they don't need to use this method.

PiperOrigin-RevId: 532188463
Change-Id: Ifb96e2b9dcd4664d57ca61d81f1fa7b7c45a8985

Improve a few type annotations in absl.flags:

1. Make `DEFINE_multi_enum_class` and `MultiEnumClassFlag` also accept `str` iterables since it's also accepted at runtime.
2. Change `get_flag_suggestions(longopt_list=)` to `Sequence`.
3. Change `flag_dict_to_args(flag_map)` to `Dict[str, Any]` because the values can be anything.

Also add a few `type: ignore`s in tests where it's explicitly testing incorrect usages for runtime.
